[b][color=red]Total Commander 8.51 Final x86-x64 + New Key | 7.96 MB[/color][/b]
 
Total Commander (former Wincmd) is a file manager for Windows similar to the Windows Explorer. But Total Commander uses a different approach: it has two fixed windows side by side like a well-known file manager for DOS.

[b]Features:[/b]

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Two file windows side by side

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Enhanced search function
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Compare files (now with editor) / synchronize directories
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Quick View panel with bitmap display
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ ZIP, ARJ, LZH, RAR, UC2, TAR, GZ, CAB, ACE archive handling + plugins
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Built-in FTP client with FXP (server to server) and HTTP proxy support
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Parallel port link, multi-rename tool
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Tabbed interface, regular expressions, history+favorites buttons
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Thumbnails view, custom columns, enhanced search
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Compare editor, cursor in lister, separate trees, logging, enhanced overwrite dialog etc.
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Unicode names almost everywhere, long names (>259 characters), password manager for ftp and plugins, synchronize empty dirs, 64 bit context menu, quick file filter (Ctrl+S)
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ New: USB port connection via special direct transfer cable, partial branch view (Ctrl+Shift+B), and many improvements to ftp, synchronizing and other functions
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ And many more!

================
 [CHANGELOG:]
================

23.04.14 Release Total Commander 8.51 final (32/64)
22.04.14 Fixed: No progress bar in system tray icon when using external icon library (via iconlib=) on high DPI device (32/64)
18.04.14 Fixed: FTP: Increased maximum allowed value of DataConnectTimeout (wcx_ftp.ini) from 60 to 300 seconds (default is 10 seconds) (32/64)
18.04.14 Fixed: Crash when aborting delete from FS plugin during the counting phase (checking how many files are in selected subfolders) (32/64)


================
[INSTALL NOTES:]
================

1. Install (x86) or (x64) version.
2. Copy key file from cRACk folder to installation folder.
3. Done
4. Enjoy!
